"The user browses View 1 at the [Overview] level and learns about the overall distribution of customer behaviors by viewing `avg_order_value` and `total_orders` across customer segments. Next, the user selects specific ranges of interest in View 1, triggering updates in exploration-level Views 2 (most purchased products) and View 5 (geographic distribution by area). The user further drills down into View 3 to explore product co-occurrence patterns and View 4 to analyze basket size distributions across customer segments. In View 6, time-based trends of product purchases are detailed, allowing the user to identify seasonality or time-dependent patterns in purchasing behavior."